Title: Quantum Deformation of the Poincare Supergroup and $\kappa$-deformed

SuperspaceAuthors: P. Kosi{\'n}ski(1), J. Lukierski(2),P. Ma{\'s}lanka(2), J.

Sobczyk(4)((1) Institute of Physics, University of Lodz , ul. Pomorska149/153, 90-236 Lodz,Poland;(2)Institute for Theoretical Physics, Universityof Wroclaw, pl. Maxa Borna 9, 50-204 Wroclaw, Poland)Comments: Wroclaw University preprint IFTUWr 868 /94, March 1994, 12 pages

Journal-ref: J.Phys. A27 (1994) 6827-6838

The classical $r$-matrix for $N=1$ superPoincar{\'e} algebra, given byLukierski, Nowicki and Sobczyk is used to describe the graded Poisson structureon the $N=1$ Poincar{\'e} supergroup. The standard correspondence principlebetween the even (odd) Poisson brackets and (anti)commutators leads to theconsistent quantum deformation of the superPoincar{\'e} group with thedeformation parameter $q$ described by fundamental mass parameter $\kappa \quad(\kappa^{-1}=\ln{q})$. The $\kappa$-deformation of $N=1$ superspace as dual tothe $\kappa$-deformed supersymmetry algebra is discussed.